#compdef vibe-log
# =============================================================================
# vibe-log — Vibelog's "Track your building journey with
#            Vibelog" — a Node.js / TypeScript CLI that
#            ingests Claude Code + Cursor + OpenAI Codex +
#            Hermes + Qoder + other AI-coding-assistant
#            session logs from their local on-disk
#            databases + JSONL files, optionally
#            sanitizes them, and uploads them to a hosted
#            dashboard for streak tracking + productivity
#            analytics + sharing of "building journeys."
#            Distinguishing from individual IDE telemetry
#            (each IDE captures its own sessions
#            independently), claude-code-router (CLI for
#            routing), and aiusage (token cost tracker)
#            by:
#              - MULTI-IDE / MULTI-AGENT INGESTION —
#                reads Claude Code's ~/.claude session
#                directory, Cursor's ~/Library/Application
#                Support/Cursor SQLite databases, OpenAI
#                Codex local sessions, and unifies them
#                into a single timeline
#              - BETTER-SQLITE3 FOR CURSOR — uses
#                better-sqlite3 (synchronous Node.js
#                SQLite bindings) to read Cursor IDE's
#                state.vscdb file, which stores
#                conversations in a SQLite database;
#                Cursor's schema includes composerId,
#                conversation messages, timestamps, and
#                versioned data (this is the headline
#                CLI library for the axis-companion role;
#                see taxonomy notes below)
#              - HOOK-BASED AUTO-SYNC — `vibe-log
#                install-auto-sync` registers shell hooks
#                with Claude Code / Cursor for automatic
#                background upload of new sessions; uses
#                Claude Code's PostToolUse + Stop hooks
#                + Cursor's hooks API where available
#              - PRIVACY SANITIZER — strips secrets,
#                tokens, API keys, paths, and PII from
#                session data before upload; `vibe-log
#                privacy` previews exactly what gets sent
#              - STATUSLINE INTEGRATION — `vibe-log
#                statusline` emits a single line of stats
#                for inclusion in shell prompts / IDE
#                statuslines (e.g., today's session count,
#                streak, recent prompt count)
#              - PROMPT ANALYSIS — `vibe-log
#                analyze-prompt` runs sentiment / quality
#                / personality classification on
#                individual prompts using a hosted LLM
#                analyzer
#              - GITHUB OAUTH AUTHENTICATION — sign in
#                with GitHub for cloud sync + web
#                dashboard + leaderboards
#              - SILENT BACKGROUND MODE — `--silent +
#                --background` flags designed for hook
#                invocation; never blocks the user's
#                shell / IDE
#              - DRY-RUN — `--dry` flag shows what would
#                be sent without uploading; useful for
#                evaluating sanitization
#              - COMMANDER CLI — uses tj/commander.js
#                (Axis 1 argparse) with nested subcommand
#                tree; aligns with most modern Node.js
#                CLIs
#              - UPDATE-NOTIFIER — uses sindresorhus/
#                update-notifier to nudge users about
#                new versions
#              - CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR ENVIRONMENT — accepts
#                Claude Code's $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR
#                environment variable for hook-context
#                project resolution
#            Used by: AI-assisted developers tracking
#            their productivity across Claude Code + Cursor
#            + Codex sessions, teams comparing AI-pair-
#            programming usage patterns, and engineers
#            participating in Vibelog's leaderboards +
#            streak system.
#
